Subject: writing X apps in C++? You need OI !!

I just downloaded the OI package and I have to say I'm very pleased. It's the
FULL WORKS of the commercial tool that I paid $$$ for on my SUN. Not
crippleware in any way!! It's even one version ahead of the one I pay for :-(

If you're into writing applications for X (OpenLook or Motif) and you use C++
I can strongly recommend you get this package and look at it carefully.

It may not be to everybody's taste - you wont see Xt... anything for example
as it replaces everything except xlib. But it surely is a fast way to make
x-apps!!

With enthusiasm, Nigel

PS:: I have no relation with parcPlace except being (obviously I suppose) a
pleased user of their product on my SUN system.

